# S08-T14: Code Quality Gate

## Objective
Conformance pass over all S08 new code against `../CODE-QUALITY.md` (piano-keyboard-export bar).
No new features — only refactors to meet the standard.

## Acceptance Criteria
- Every new component: `memo` + `.displayName`; variant components use discriminated-union props.
- Every new hook: typed options object, returns named object, cleans up tweens/RAF/listeners.
- Pure logic lives in `src/game/`; no React imports there.
- No magic numbers in engine/animation — extracted to named, doc'd constants.
- Brand colours only via S01 tokens (no raw hex in new JSX/CSS).
- A11y: new buttons are real `<button>` with `aria-*`; decorative SVG `aria-hidden`; focus-visible.
- Public components/hooks/utils have JSDoc; non-trivial ones an `@example`.
- `tsc --noEmit` clean; ESLint clean (no new disables); zero console errors in both modes.

## Steps
1. Walk each S08 file; checklist against `CODE-QUALITY.md` "Mandatory bar".
2. Refactor offenders (extract consts, add displayName/JSDoc, fix a11y, ensure cleanup).
3. Run `tsc --noEmit` + lint; fix all findings.
4. Write a short `S08-QUALITY-PASS.md` (file-by-file pass/notes).
5. `git commit -m "chore(quality): S08 conformance to code-quality standard"`.
